  "texts": [
    "Various synthesis methods have been employed in attempts to produce BFO, including solid-state reactions [26][27][28], sol-gel processes [29,30], and autocombustion methods [31].",
    "However, the precise phase composition in the Bi 2 O 3 -F e 2 O 3 system is highly sensitive to small deviations from the ideal stoichiometric ratio [22].",
    "For example, a slight deviation to the left of the phase diagram gives sillenite phases, whereas mullite-like phases are likely, whereas the precursor deviates to the right.Although phase-pure BiF eO 3 can theoretically be achieved through careful stoichiometric control, this remains challenging due to the sensitivity of phase composition to precursor ratios, synthesis temperature, annealing history and the presence of impurities [31].",
    "Despite extensive efforts to refine the synthesis of pure-phase BFO and explore its thermodynamic behaviour, the phase diagram remains unclear.",
    "Although there is general consensus that the BiF eO 3 phase is thermodynamically stable over a wide temperature range, conflicting reports persist [32]."
  ],
